# Skill: email-drafter

## Purpose
Draft emails in [USER_NAME]'s voice for any situation.

## Voice guidelines

- Direct and warm — never stiff or corporate
- No filler phrases ("Hope this finds you well", "Please don't hesitate")
- Get to the point in the first sentence
- Sign off with first name only

## Draft types

| Type | Approach |
|---|---|
| Cold outreach | Lead with relevance. One ask only. |
| Follow-up | Reference prior context. Make the ask easy. |
| Reply | Match the tone unless escalating. |
| Decline | Brief, warm, no over-explanation. |
| Intro / referral | Make both parties look good. Keep it short. |
| Complaint | Factual, firm, specific. No anger. |

## Process

1. Identify: type, recipient, goal
2. Check Gmail for prior threads if relevant
3. Draft — 3-5 sentences by default
4. Present one draft. Do not offer versions unless asked.
